Title: Creation of Query to Identify Students with 30+ IAI Eligible Credits
Purpose:
To identify students who have accumulated at least 30 credit hours in courses that meet Illinois Articulation Initiative (IAI) requirements and meet local government code restrictions.

SQL Code Created

SELECT stc_person_id, SUM(stc_cred)
FROM student_acad_cred sac
JOIN course_sections_ls cs
  ON '*' || sac.stc_term || '*' || sac.stc_course_name || '-' || sac.stc_section_no
     = cs.sec_section_idx
 AND cs.pos = 1
LEFT JOIN courses c
  ON sac.stc_course_name = c.crs_name
WHERE cs.sec_local_govt_codes = '11'
  AND c.crs_standard_articulation_no LIKE 'IAI%'
  AND (
        sac.stc_term IN ('2025FA','2025SU','2025SP')
        OR sac.stc_term IS NULL
      )
  AND (
        sac.stc_cum_contrib_grade_pts > 1
        OR (sac.stc_term IS NULL AND sac.stc_verified_grade = '49')
      )
GROUP BY stc_person_id
HAVING SUM(stc_cred) > 29.5;

Added: 3/16/26
Credit calculation:

Original: SUM only included last-year courses.

Updated: SUM now includes all qualifying courses across all terms.

Student selection:

Original: Filtered directly on stc_term in the main query.

Updated: Added subquery to select students enrolled in the last year.

Reason: Preserves last-year enrollment requirement while summing all credits.

Join to sections:

Original: Outer query joined course_sections_ls.

Updated: Outer query no longer joins sections; subquery handles section filtering.

Reason: Reduces duplication and allows cumulative sum.

Transfer & GPA rules:

Original: Applied in main WHERE.

Updated: Still applied in main WHERE.

Reason: Logic for counting valid credits is preserved.

Terms filter:

Original: Included terms directly in main WHERE.

Updated: Moved to subquery for student selection.

Reason: Ensures cumulative credits count all terms, not just last-year courses.

Performance / clarity:

Original query limited scope and summed only last-year credits.

Updated query separates student selection from credit summation, improving clarity and matching intended logic.
